lyrics:
[Verse]
Mardy bum, sitting in the corner, looking down
With your sulking eyes and that melancholic frown
You say you're tired of all this town has been
But darling, let's find a way to break the routine

[Chorus]
Oh mardy bum, let's dance through the pouring rain
Leave this world behind, feel alive again
Don't let the weight of the world drown your soul
Just let the music guide us and make us whole
